        "content": "<p>I realized I should probably use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=modelWithCornersEuclideanHalfSpace#doc\">docs#modelWithCornersEuclideanHalfSpace</a>, and then formalize the notion of regular surface etc.</p>\n<p>At the moment there doesn't seem to be much on surfaces and curves in Mathlib, and I don't feel confident enough to work with the abstract manifold setting just yet. maybe I'll try to look at some classical differential geometry textbooks (e.g. do Carmo) and see how far I can go with those in lean. If anyone has any suggestions please let me know!</p>",
